HEADWORD: Pygopodes
<hw>Py*gop"o*des</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of swimming birds
which includes the grebes, divers, auks, etc., in which the legs are
placed far back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pygopodous</ent>⟦br⟧
